<title>NETHERLANDS: Suez reiterates Aegon as a Buy.</title>
<headline>Suez reiterates Aegon as a Buy.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-01-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Summary of Jan 2 research.</p>
<p>Company---------Sector--------Price---Broker----------------</p>
<p>    Aegon	     Insurance     108.80  Suez Nederland</p>
<p>COMMENT: Buy (reiterates). Aegon to pay $3.5 billion for Providian insurance, which will enable it to grow faster in the U.S. and due to a perfect synergy, cost savings are expected to be an annual $100 million. Aegon is the most expensive Dutch financial stock but it is the only one able to deliver a 15 percent EPS growth in the coming years. The highly predictable life insurance business is the major factor. Aegon will become the fourth biggest life insurer in the U.S.</p>
<p>    Estimates (Dfl):   EPS	pvs	P/E     Dividend</p>
<p>    1995 (actual)	 5.04		 14.1     2.37</p>
<p>    1996		    5.85		 18.8     2.75</p>
<p>    1997		    6.75		 16.1     3.17</p>
<p>    1998		    7.85   (7.50)    13.9     3.68</p>
